Add files via upload

The program will create a CSV file where each row contains a sequence and its corresponding label. They will be labeled as 1 for positive case input and 0 for negative examples respectively. The CSV file will have two columns. The script can be run as follows: 
python data_labeling.py <bed_file> <output_csv>

Create ExtractSequences.py

Make sure to have the pyfaidx library installed, and run the script with the BED file and reference genome specified as command-line arguments.

The script will extract the DNA sequence of the BED file in one column and generate negative examples (with avoided regions) in another column.
